  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: App asks for camera access and than for microphone access when try to scan QR code or capture an image for 1st time. It's expected to get only camera access question.\r\nNote: if user denies microphone access then there popup that instructs how to enable access for camera. So, if user allows access to camera but denies access to microphone then on each attempt to scan QR user will be instructed to enable access to camera (that is already enabled).\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what you expected to happen.)\r\nApp asks only for camera access when try to scan QR code or capture an image for 1st time\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what actually happened.)\r\nApp asks only for camera access and for microphone access when try to scan QR code or capture an image for 1st time\r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\nVideo: https://drive.google.com/open?id=0Bz3t9zSg1wb7bWpYZWhpWkd1VGc\r\n- Run Status 1st time\r\n- Contacts -> New Contact -> Scan QR\r\n- Deny access to Camera\r\n- Open Device Settings -> Status -> give access to camera\r\n- In Status: Contacts -> New Contact -> Scan QR. Now App asks access to microphone but there is no need in microphone for QR scan.\r\nExpected: Microphone access is not asked. It can be asked when user tries to use Instabug feature but not when scan QR or capture profile image\r\n![microphone access](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/6584810/25654989/943fa0c0-2ff3-11e7-9932-847b34187e77.jpg)\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\r\n* Status version: 0.9.7d38\r\n* Operating System: iOS only\r\n\r\n",
